\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]] Udo Coach...

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Nfufu~♪ Finally,

congratulations on reaching this room~

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] Enough with the

done to the three of them?

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Three people? What are
you talking about?

\n<Minato Neon>Don't play dumb! It's Kino, Sawa, and Momo, the
three of them!
I confront Coach Udo and grab him by the collar.

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Ah... I see, you're
talking about the video. Come to think of it, I
did mention their names in the 4P video, so it's
no wonder you noticed (laughs).
\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...You bastard!

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Hey, Neon-chan... Are
you misunderstanding something?

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...Huh? You think I'm
mistaken?

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] You're treating me like
the bad guy, but... let me ask you this... did any
of them show any signs of discomfort?

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] That's... but, to treat
them so cruelly...

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Even if it's measured
by Neon-chan's standards... those girls had their
desires and I simply fulfilled them... That's all
there is to it.

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Besides... even if
they're friends, isn't it presumptuous to meddle
in their relationship with each other? They're not
children, you know?
\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...

I... I'm at a loss for words. My anger fades away
in the face of Coach Udo's unexpected
counterattack.

\n<Udo Takeru>But well... I can't say I don't understand Neon-
chan's point of view. In society, it's considered
an impure act, and above all, they are important
friends.

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] That's why I think
'understanding' is necessary. If you truly care
about and value them, I think you should first
understand how they came to accept me, don't you
think?

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...Huh? How would
you...?

\n<Udo Takeru>Well, it's a simple matter... You just have to
test whether you yourself can accept me or not.

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] If... you are able to
reject me, then you will be in the right. At that
time, I will end my relationship with the three of
them and take on the appropriate responsibility.

\n<Udo Takeru>On the contrary, if Neon-chan were to accept me,
wouldn't that dispel your doubts and bring peace
of mind to Neon-chan as well?

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] (Test whether I can
accept him? What are you talking about...)

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Huh? Don't you get it?
Well then, let me put it in a way that suits us
better.

\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] It's the final lesson,
Neon-chan♪ The stakes are your 'first and only
chance to prove your righteousness♪ Will you
accept it?
\n<Udo Takeru>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Nfufufufu♪

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] (So that's what it is...
Whether I will cross the final line or not...)

I didn't feel inclined to reject that proposal.
Maybe it's because the situation was already
unfavorable... but I thought it would be much
easier to understand than continuing to argue back
and forth.

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] (It might be a big
concern for the three of them... but... I just
can't see that kind of relationship as normal...)

\n<Udo Takeru>Of course... it's fine if you run away from the
competition because you can't bear to lose to my
cuteness, you know? No one will complain, and it's
not a competition that is only done to understand
our comrades, right?

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]]\FF[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...I'll accept it, don't
underestimate me. The words of withdrawing from
the three of you... never forget them.

\n<Udo Takeru>Nfufufu, that's right, Neon-chan♪ Well then, I'll
go ahead to the bedroom first, okay?
